	   <tr><td colspan=2>Unfortunately, putting spawns on long timers is Verant's solution to controlling the flow of items into the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;The worst of these, from what I've personally seen, are the Ragefire camp for the Cleric epic and Lodizal for the Eyepatch quest.  JBoots in South Ro is very frustrating, because it's a wandering spawn with a varying spawn point, and therefore not even remotely campable.  Mostly you will get people respecting the OOT camp, tho - with exceptions.<br><br>I'm not sure how I would change the current system, though.  An encounter that is a good challenge for a mid-to-high level guild is trivial for an end-game guild.  Without timers on spawns, the top guilds would just farm a spawn until they had loot rotting.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
